BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Introduction) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 690.0 Td (Your gut is often called your 'second brain' - and for good reason. The gut microbiome) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 676.0 Td (influences everything from digestion and immunity to mental health and energy levels. If) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 662.0 Td (you're experiencing bloating, irregular bowel movements, food sensitivities, or) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 648.0 Td (unexplained fatigue, your gut health may need attention.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 624.2 Td (This workbook provides a structured approach to identifying food triggers, healing your) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 610.2 Td (gut lining, and rebuilding a healthy microbiome through diet and lifestyle changes.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 582.4 Td (Who This Book Is For) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 566.4 Td (- People with IBS, bloating, or chronic digestive issues) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 552.4 Td (- Those suspecting food sensitivities or intolerances) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 538.4 Td (- Anyone recovering from antibiotic use or gut infections) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 524.4 Td (- People with autoimmune conditions linked to gut health) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 510.4 Td (- Anyone wanting to optimize their microbiome) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
