102 0 obj
<< /Length 2901 >>
stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Frequently Asked Questions) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 676.2 Td (Q: How long does gut healing take?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 660.2 Td (It varies by individual. Most people see improvement in 2-4 weeks, but full healing of gut) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 646.2 Td (lining can take 3-6 months. Consistency is key.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 618.4 Td (Q: Do I need a probiotic supplement?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 602.4 Td (Food-based probiotics are preferred. If supplementing, choose a multi-strain probiotic) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 588.4 Td (with at least 10 billion CFUs. Start slowly to avoid die-off symptoms.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 560.6 Td (Q: What is leaky gut?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 544.6 Td (Intestinal permeability \('leaky gut'\) occurs when tight junctions in the gut lining) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 530.6 Td (weaken, allowing particles to enter the bloodstream and trigger immune reactions.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 502.8 Td (Q: Can stress really affect my gut?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 486.8 Td (Absolutely. The gut-brain axis is a bidirectional communication system. Stress can change) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 472.8 Td (gut motility, increase permeability, and alter the microbiome within hours.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 445.0 Td (Q: Should I get tested for food sensitivities?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 429.0 Td (Testing can be helpful but is not always accurate. The gold standard remains an) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 415.0 Td (elimination diet with careful reintroduction and symptom tracking.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 387.2 Td (Q: How do I know if I need medical help?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 371.2 Td (See a doctor if you have blood in stool, unexplained weight loss, severe pain, fever, or) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 357.2 Td (symptoms that don't improve after 4-6 weeks of dietary changes.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 329.4 Td (Q: Is bone broth really beneficial?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 313.4 Td (Yes. Bone broth contains collagen, glutamine, glycine, and gelatin - all of which support) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 299.4 Td (gut lining repair and reduce inflammation.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 271.6 Td (Q: Can I heal my gut while on medications?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 255.6 Td (Yes, though some medications \(PPIs, NSAIDs, antibiotics\) can slow healing. Never stop) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 241.6 Td (medications without medical guidance.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 213.8 Td (Q: What about FODMAPs?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 197.8 Td (If you have IBS, a low-FODMAP diet may help identify specific carbohydrate triggers.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 183.8 Td (Consider working with a registered dietitian for this protocol.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 156.0 Td (Q: How do I rebuild my microbiome after antibiotics?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 140.0 Td (Focus on diverse fiber intake, fermented foods, and possibly a probiotic supplement for) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 126.0 Td (2-3 months. Eat 30+ different plant foods per week.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
